om Flaming Red by Patty Griffin and 10 Cent Wings by Jonatha Brooke.[167] Perry intends to become "more of a Joni Mitchell", releasing folk and acoustic music.[168] Perry's autobiographical documentary Katy Perry: Part of Me was largely influenced by Madonna: Truth or Dare. She admires Madonna's ability to reinvent herself, saying "I want to evolve like Madonna."[169]

Perry has listed multiple artists as having inspired her work. She names Gwen Stefani and Björk as influences, particularly admiring Björk's "willingness to always be taking chances".[167] "Firework" was inspired by a passage in the book On the Road by Jack Kerouac in which the author compares people who are full of life to fireworks that shoot across the sky and make people watch in awe.[170] Her second concert tour, the California Dreams Tour, was reminiscent of Alice in Wonderland and The Wizard of Oz.[171] She also credits the 1996 movie The Craft for being the influence behind her song "Dark Horse",[172] and Eckhart Tolle's book The Powe
